$interpreted: Teenager: Don't cry, Miranda...smile, won't you?
Teenager: Your smile is bright and warm, like the sun. I like it so much.
Teenager: ...Just like this...
Miranda: Fell asleep in the tree without even knowing it...
Miranda: ...No dewdrops at night...?
Miranda: What's that noise?
Miranda: The matriarch said this place was desolate. No one should be here, right...?
Miranda: (Is that...Fatima?)
Fatima: First...walk one step forward and lift the branch up high...
Miranda: ...*snickers*...
Fatima: Who's there!?
Fatima: (Ah! I shouldn't have spoken...)
Miranda: It's me, Miss Fatima! I'm sorry. I didn't mean to be spying on you~
Miranda: But now I know that you can talk!
Fatima: ...Obviously.
Miranda: So why didn't you speak before?
Miranda: What are you doing in such a remote place in the middle of the night?
Fatima: Seeing that I've been discovered by you, I might as well speak the truth. But, if you dare tell anyone...
Miranda: Of course not! I'll keep your secret!
Fatima: Hmph.
Fatima: The Panthers' quadrennial Inheritance Ritual is coming up in a few days. I have been chosen to serve as the Cybin.
Miranda: Cybin?
Fatima: I guess for you guys it's like a preistly ambassador. On that day, I'll be required to put on a priestess' robe and carry the Blessed Branch as I dance.
Fatima: And...I may not speak to anyone for one hundred days.
Fatima: But...
Miranda: But I ruined it for you, didn't I? Caused you to break your vow of silence.
Miranda: ...Eh, you weren't secretly practicing how to dance, were you?
Fatima: .......
Miranda: Seriously!?
Fatima: ...I am used to battle, but I have no idea how to dance.
Fatima: If you dare tell anyone about this...
Miranda: Miss F-F-F-Fatima!?
Miranda: This...
Fatima: Sometimes they'll show up around here. Watch yourself!
Miranda: You really are used to battle. Thanks~
Fatima: Don't mention it. This is my responsibilty as captain. After all, the matriarch said to treat you as a guest.
Fatima: Apologies for disturbing your rest. I will go somewhere else.
Fatima: During the day you said you wanted to borrow some sort of wooden tablet. There's nothing of the sort here.
Fatima: I'm not sure why you've come, but don't think that your human lies will work on the Panthers.
Miranda: But, everything I've said is the truth.
Fatima: We'll see about that when the matriarch checks the ancestral records tomorrow. Everything will come to light.
Miranda: ...The matriarch...her memory doesn't seem so good. What if she finds the wrong manuscript?
Fatima: You dare disrespect the matriarch!
Miranda: I'm s-sorry, Miss Fatima!
Fatima: Hmph!
Fatima: This is your final warning. If you dare...
Miranda: I will absolutely, definitely not tell anyone! I promise!
Miranda: This feeling...is worth remembering.
